HEADWORD: Penetrable
<hw>Pen"e*tra*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>penetrabilus</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>p⟦eacute⟧n⟦eacute⟧trable</ets>.]</ety> <def>Capable of being
penetrated, entered, or pierced. Used also figuratively.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And pierce his only <qex>penetrable</qex> part.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I am not made of stones,⟦br⟧
But <qex>penetrable</qex> to your kind entreats.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Pen"e*tra*ble*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos> --
<wf>Pen"e*tra*bly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Penetrail</ent>⟦br⟧
